                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/650a.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-01T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">June</hi> 1, 1912—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You will instruct consular officers to keep Legation and Department informed by
                    telegraph on Monday and Thursday of each week of movement of Cuban and
                    revolutionary forces in their districts.</p>
                <p>You will at once endeavor to have the Cuban Government station and maintain
                    regular guards of 200 men each at both Daiquiri and Firmenza and of 50 men at El
                    Cobre for the protection of the Spanish-American, the Juraguá, and Cuba Copper
                    companies. This is most important.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
